[src:fmt-cpp-lib/string-interpolation] String interpolation is common in many programming languages which make heavy use of string representations of data, such as Apache Groovy, Julia, Kotlin, Perl, PHP, Python, Ruby, Scala, Swift, Tcl and most Unix shells.
[src:fmt-cpp-lib/string-interpolation] *Split and join string*: splitting the string into an array, merging it with the corresponding array of values, then joining items by concatenation.
